# 🏀 Sports Buddy

**Sports Buddy** is a web application that helps users discover and organize sports events near them. It supports user registration, login, event creation, and admin controls like managing cities, areas, and categories.

---

## 🌐 Live Demo

> 🔗 [Add your Firebase Hosting URL here after deploying]

---

## 🚀 Features

### 👤 Users
- Register and login securely
- Add sports events with city, area, date/time, and category
- View all upcoming events
- Edit or delete their added events

### 👨‍💼 Admins
- Login as admin
- Add/update:
  - Sports categories
  - Cities
  - Areas

---

## 🧰 Technologies Used

- **HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)**
- **Firebase Authentication**
- **Firebase Firestore (Database)**
- **Firebase Hosting**

---

## 📦 Folder Structure

project-root/
│
├── index.html # Main HTML file
├── style.css # Styling
├── javascript.js # Main logic and Firebase integration
├── firebaseConfig.js # Firebase project config
└── README.md # Project instructions and documentation

Make sure your Firebase project is set up:

Go to Firebase Console

Create a new project

Enable Authentication (Email/Password)

Create Cloud Firestore

Replace Firebase config in firebaseConfig.js with your project credentials.

Open index.html in your browser and test.


Firebase Hosting Deployment
Install Firebase CL

npm install -g firebase-tools
Login to Firebase

firebase login
Initialize Firebase

firebase init
Choose:

Hosting

Select your Firebase project

Set public directory as .

Say No to SPA rewrite

Deploy

firebase deploy

Project Evaluation Criteria
✅ Modular, testable, maintainable, portable code

✅ Proper Firebase integration for Auth and Firestore

✅ Logging via console.log() and alerts

✅ Public GitHub repository with documentation

✅ Firebase-hosted project with working demo

